        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(memory): distinguish QMD search outcomes",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #96796.\n\nThis PR separates QMD search outcomes from plain zero-hit results so `memory_search` no longer treats every empty QMD result as a stale index signal. It also carries the follow-up fixes found during local runtime activation: internal subagent session keys now pass QMD direct-chat scope, and the fallback memory manager preserves `searchWithOutcome()` instead of dropping back to the legacy `search()`-only path.\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nPreviously, `QmdMemoryManager.search()` returned `[]` for multiple distinct states, including policy/guard outcomes such as scope denial. The `memory_search` caller could not distinguish those states and could force `sync({ reason: \"search\", force: true })`, causing slow interactive searches even when the index was already clean or the search was denied.\n\nDuring local activation, two adjacent runtime faults were confirmed:\n\n- Subagent session keys such as `agent:vision:subagent:*` were normalized to `subagent:*`, then rejected by direct-chat QMD scope rules.\n- A fallback wrapper could omit `searchWithOutcome()`, allowing callers to fall back to the old ambiguous zero-result behavior after QMD fallback.\n\n## What Changed\n\n- Adds shared memory search outcome types:\n  - `MemorySearchOptions`\n  - `MemorySearchOutcome`\n  - `MemorySearchOutcomeResult`\n- Adds optional `MemorySearchManager.searchWithOutcome()`.\n- Keeps the existing `search(): Promise<MemorySearchResult[]>` contract compatible.\n- Implements `QmdMemoryManager.searchWithOutcome()` with discriminated outcomes:\n  - `ok`\n  - `scope-denied`\n  - `empty-query`\n  - `no-collections`\n- Updates `memory_search` to use detailed outcomes when available.\n- Preserves legacy fallback behavior for managers without `searchWithOutcome()`.\n- Gates forced sync after zero hits to detailed QMD searches where:\n  - `outcome === \"ok\"`\n  - `hits.length === 0`\n  - `status().dirty === true`\n- Treats internal `agent:<id>:subagent:<uuid>` session keys as direct QMD scope instead of unknown/denied scope.\n- Threads `searchWithOutcome()` through `FallbackMemoryManager`, including builtin fallback wrapping for managers that only implement `search()`.\n\n## Evidence\n\nInitial PR validation:\n\n```bash\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.extension-memory.config.ts extensions/memory-core/src/tools.test.ts extensions/memory-core/src/memory/qmd-manager.test.ts\n```\n\nResult:\n\n- 2 test files passed\n- 159 tests passed\n\n```bash\npnpm test:extensions:package-boundary:compile\n```\n\nResult:\n\n- extension package boundary check passed\n- 116 plugins compiled\n\nAdditional local validation after follow-up fixes:\n\n```bash\n./node_modules/.bin/oxlint extensions/memory-core/src/memory/search-manager.ts extensions/memory-core/src/memory/search-manager.test.ts packages/memory-host-sdk/src/host/qmd-scope.ts packages/memory-host-sdk/src/host/qmd-scope.test.ts\n```\n\nResult:\n\n- 0 warnings\n- 0 errors\n\n```bash\n./node_modules/.bin/vitest run extensions/memory-core/src/memory/search-manager.test.ts packages/memory-host-sdk/src/host/qmd-scope.test.ts extensions/memory-core/src/memory/qmd-manager.test.ts extensions/memory-core/src/tools.test.ts\n```\n\nResult in this local clone:\n\n- `packages/memory-host-sdk/src/host/qmd-scope.test.ts`: 7 passed\n- memory-core suites did not execute because this clone is missing `@openclaw/fs-safe/config` during test import, before the affected tests run. CI is expected to provide the full workspace dependency graph.\n\nRuntime activation evidence from the downstream hotfix environment:\n\n- `memory_search` passes for `corpus=memory`, `corpus=all`, and `corpus=sessions`.\n- QMD main is clean (`dirty=no`), with 7845 chunks and 24 collections.\n- No active `qmd embed` or `qmd sync` processes.\n- No recent `ensureOpen`, `Cannot read properties`, `qmd search denied by scope`, or `reason=search` logs after the hotfix restart.\n",
        "branch": "fix/qmd-memory-search-outcomes",
